.TH GIT-REWRITE 1 "13 November 2025" "git-rewrite 0.1.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
git-rewrite \- amend any commit in git history with staged changes
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B git-rewrite
.I commit-id
.RI [ options ]

.SH DESCRIPTION
.B git-rewrite
is a small helper that amends a specific commit (identified by
.I commit-id ) using the currently staged changes and then rebases any later
commits to preserve history. It uses Git's fixup/autosquash workflow and
pauses for manual conflict resolution if necessary.

.SH OPTIONS
.TP
\fB-m, --message\fR \fItext\fR
Replace the amended commit message with \fItext\fR.

.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
Amend a commit with staged changes:
.RS
.B git-rewrite abc1234
.RE

.SH SEE ALSO
git(1), git-rebase(1)

.SH AUTHOR
Written by the git-rewrite project.
